(4)I understand the Annual Gross Salary.
Annual Gross Salary is included allowance?
For example)
Month salary
8,000,000 / (12 + 2)(If the bonus is twice) = 570,000(Pre-tax)
570,000 * 0.8(resident tax, income tax, employment insurance (company burden), industrial accident insurance(company burden), health insurance, social insurance premiums)
= 450,000(After-tax)
450,000 + 30,000 + 60,000
= 540,000 (This case is that Annual Gross Salary is not included allowance)
or
570,000 - (30,000 + 60,000) = 480,000(Pre-tax)
480,000 * 0.8(resident tax, income tax, employment insurance (company burden), industrial accident insurance(company burden), health insurance, social insurance premiums)
= 380,000(After-tax)
380,000 + 30,000 + 60,000 = 470,000(This case is that Annual Gross Salary is included allowance)

※The tax is that depends on company income, income(my salary), number of dependents.The standard tax calculation is 20%.

